backend.grid.BoundsHandler.name: Infinite Bounds
backend.grid.BoundsHandler.description: Allows grid to expand to accommodate out of bounds coordinates.

backend.grid.BoundsHandler.name: Toroidal Bounds
backend.grid.BoundsHandler.description: Wraps out of bounds coordinates to the opposite side of the grid

backend.grid.BoundsHandler.description: Converts out of bounds coordinates to the closest inbounds coordinate on a square grid.

backend.grid.BoundsHandler.name: Finite Bounds
backend.grid.BoundsHandler.description: Converts out of bounds coordinates to the closest inbounds coordinate on the grid.

backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.name: Blind
backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.description: The attacker gives any neighboring unit the Blinded modifier

range.name: Square Adjacent
range.description: This pattern of square coordinates is composed of all square coordinates adjacent to the origin.

backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.name: Silence
backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.description: Removes all temporary abilities from any neighboring unit

backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.name: Consume
backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.description: The attacker deals damage to the defender. If the defender dies, the user heals for the amount of damage dealt, and the user takes the defender's place. (Does not count as movement)

backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.name: Suicide Squad, Attack!
backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.description: The attacker sacrifices itself to deal massive damage to all neighboring enemy units.

backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.name: Sword
backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.description: The attacker hits 3 times for 5 damage on any neighboring unit

backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.name: Full Heal
backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.description: The attacker fully heals any neighboring unit

backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.name: Bow
backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.description: The attacker hits 2 times for 7 dmage on any unit in a straight line away from the attacker

range.name: Square Rays
range.description: This pattern of square coordinates is composed of all square coordinates on 4 rays centered at the origin

backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.name: Set Fire to Cell
backend.unit.properties.ActiveAbility.description: The attacker sets fire to the cell they are occupying.

range.name: Square Single Cell
range.description: This pattern contains a single square cell at the origin

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Movepoints are consumed by moving on the map. Difficult terrain costs more movepoints, while more mobile units have more to spare.

backend.grid.GridPattern.name: Hexagonal Adjacent
backend.grid.GridPattern.description: This pattern of hexagonal coordinates is composed of all hexagonal coordinates adjacent to the origin.

backend.grid.GridPattern.name: Hexagonal Rays
backend.grid.GridPattern.description: This pattern of hexagonal coordinates is composed of all hexagonal coordinates on 6 rays centered at the origin.

backend.grid.GridPattern.name: Hexagonal Single Cell

backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.name: First Blood
backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.description: Attacks do extra damage to targets at full HP.

backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.name: Weakened
backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.description: Attacks do extra damage if the defender has more HP than the attacker.

backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.name: Blinded
backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.description: Attacks have a high chance to miss

backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.name: Lawful
backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.description: Attacks do more damage in daytime, but less damage in nighttime

backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.name: Assassin
backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.description: Attacks do extra damage to isolated units with no nearby allies

backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.name: Executioner
backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.description: Attacks do extra damage to targets at low HP.

backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.name: Critical Strike
backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.description: Attacks have a chance to critical strike, hitting for extra damage.

backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.name: Chaotic
backend.unit.properties.InteractionModif.description: Attacks do more damage in nighttime, but less damage in daytime.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Poisoned
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit is poisoned, and will lose 4 damage at the run and end of each turn, to a minimum of 1 HP. Lasts for 6 turns

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Regeneration
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit regenerates 6 HP at the run of each turn.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Regenerate Energy Points
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit regenerates some energy points at the beginning of each turn.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Reset Move Points

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Healer

activeAbilities.name: Active Abilities
activeAbilities.description: Each unit has a set of active abilities which the user can use on the users' own turn.

triggeredAbilities.name: Triggered abilities
triggeredAbilities.description: Each unit has passive abilities that automatically trigger in response to certain events in the game. Note that not all triggered abilities are positive.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Reset Ability Points
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit regains full ability points at the beginning of each turn.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Reset Move Points
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit regains full movepoints at the beginning of each turn.

offensiveModifiers.name: Offensive Modifiers
offensiveModifiers.description: Each unit has a set of offensive modifiers that can change the amount of damage the unit deals under different conditions.

defensiveModifiers.name: Defensive modifiers
defensiveModifiers.description: Each unit has a set of defensive modifiers that can change the amount of damage the unit receives under different conditions.

stats.name: Unit stats
stats.description: Each unit has its own set of numerical stats, such as hitpoints or movement points.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Ability Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Most active abilities use ability points. They limit the number of actions a unit can do each turn.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Gold
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Players have a limited amount of gold to spend on their units.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Energy
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Energy points are required for and consumed by some powerful abilities.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Hit Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Units lose HP when taking damage. When a unit's hitpoints reach 0, the unit dies.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Move Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Movepoints are consumed by moving on the map. Difficult terrain costs more movepoints, while more mobile units have more to spare.

activeAbilities.name: Active Abilities
activeAbilities.description: Each unit has a set of active abilities which the user can use on the users' own turn.

triggeredAbilities.name: Triggered abilities
triggeredAbilities.description: Each unit has passive abilities that automatically trigger in response to certain events in the game. Note that not all triggered abilities are positive.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Reset Ability Points
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit regains full ability points at the beginning of each turn.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Reset Move Points
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit regains full movepoints at the beginning of each turn.

offensiveModifiers.name: Offensive Modifiers
offensiveModifiers.description: Each unit has a set of offensive modifiers that can change the amount of damage the unit deals under different conditions.

defensiveModifiers.name: Defensive modifiers
defensiveModifiers.description: Each unit has a set of defensive modifiers that can change the amount of damage the unit receives under different conditions.

stats.name: Unit stats
stats.description: Each unit has its own set of numerical stats, such as hitpoints or movement points.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Ability Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Most active abilities use ability points. They limit the number of actions a unit can do each turn.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Gold
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Players have a limited amount of gold to spend on their units.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Energy
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Energy points are required for and consumed by some powerful abilities.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Hit Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Units lose HP when taking damage. When a unit's hitpoints reach 0, the unit dies.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Move Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Movepoints are consumed by moving on the map. Difficult terrain costs more movepoints, while more mobile units have more to spare.

activeAbilities.name: Active Abilities
activeAbilities.description: Each unit has a set of active abilities which the user can use on the users' own turn.

triggeredAbilities.name: Triggered abilities
triggeredAbilities.description: Each unit has passive abilities that automatically trigger in response to certain events in the game. Note that not all triggered abilities are positive.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Reset Ability Points
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit regains full ability points at the beginning of each turn.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Reset Move Points
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit regains full movepoints at the beginning of each turn.

offensiveModifiers.name: Offensive Modifiers
offensiveModifiers.description: Each unit has a set of offensive modifiers that can change the amount of damage the unit deals under different conditions.

defensiveModifiers.name: Defensive modifiers
defensiveModifiers.description: Each unit has a set of defensive modifiers that can change the amount of damage the unit receives under different conditions.

stats.name: Unit stats
stats.description: Each unit has its own set of numerical stats, such as hitpoints or movement points.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Ability Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Most active abilities use ability points. They limit the number of actions a unit can do each turn.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Gold
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Players have a limited amount of gold to spend on their units.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Energy
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Energy points are required for and consumed by some powerful abilities.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Hit Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Units lose HP when taking damage. When a unit's hitpoints reach 0, the unit dies.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Move Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Movepoints are consumed by moving on the map. Difficult terrain costs more movepoints, while more mobile units have more to spare.

activeAbilities.name: Active Abilities
activeAbilities.description: Each unit has a set of active abilities which the user can use on the users' own turn.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Reset Ability Points
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit regains full ability points at the beginning of each turn.

backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.name: Reset Move Points
backend.util.ModifiableTriggeredEffect.description: This unit regains full movepoints at the beginning of each turn.

offensiveModifiers.name: Offensive Modifiers
offensiveModifiers.description: Each unit has a set of offensive modifiers that can change the amount of damage the unit deals under different conditions.

defensiveModifiers.name: Defensive modifiers
defensiveModifiers.description: Each unit has a set of defensive modifiers that can change the amount of damage the unit receives under different conditions.

stats.name: Unit stats
stats.description: Each unit has its own set of numerical stats, such as hitpoints or movement points.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Ability Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Most active abilities use ability points. They limit the number of actions a unit can do each turn.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Gold
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Players have a limited amount of gold to spend on their units.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Energy
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Energy points are required for and consumed by some powerful abilities.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Hit Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Units lose HP when taking damage. When a unit's hitpoints reach 0, the unit dies.

backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.name: Move Points
backend.unit.properties.ModifiableUnitSt.description: Movepoints are consumed by moving on the map. Difficult terrain costs more movepoints, while more mobile units have more to spare.
